{"cursor":"4708","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Officeholder |name = Rodolfo Severino, Jr. |image = |office = 10th\nSecretary General of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations |vicepresident =\n|term_start = 1 January 1998 |term_end = 31 December 2002 |predecessor = Ajit\nSingh |successor = Ong Keng Yong |birth_date = 27 April 1936 |birth_place =\nPhilippines |death_date = |death_place = |children = |party = |alma_mater =\nAteneo de Manila University Johns Hopkins School of Advanced International\nStudies |profession = Diplomat |religion = Roman Catholicism |website = }}\n'Rodolfo Certeza Severino, Jr.' is a Filipino diplomat and was the Secretary\nGeneral of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) from 1998 to 2002.\nHe is currently the Head of the ASEAN Studies Centre at the Institute of\nSoutheast Asian Studies in\nSingapore, http://www.aseanstudiescentre.org/ and an Adjunct Professor\nat the Lee Kuan Yew School of Public Policy, National University of Singapore. http://www.lkyspp.nus.edu.sg/Staff_Directory_Faculty_Research.aspx He\nis the author of four books: Southeast Asia in Search of an ASEAN Community\n(2006), ASEAN (2008), The ASEAN Regional Forum (2009) and Where in the World is\nthe Philippines? (2010). http://www.aseanstudiescentre.org/ He is also\nthe co-editor of Whither the Philippines in the 21st Century? (2007). http://www.amazon.com/Whither-Philippines-Century-Rodolfo-\nSeverino/dp/9812304991/ref=pd_ybh_1\n\nHe studied at Ateneo de Manila University and he holds a post-graduate degree\nin International Studies from the Johns Hopkins School of Advanced\nInternational Studies.\n\nHe previously held the following positions http://www.asian-\naffairs.com/biographies/severinocv.html http://www.iseas.edu.sg/asean-\nstudiescentre/whoswho.htm *Third, Second, and First Secretary, Philippine\nEmbassy in Washington, D.C. (1967-1974) *Special Assistant to the Undersecretary\nof Foreign Affairs, Foreign Affairs (1974-1976) *Minister-Counsellor and ChargÃ©\ndâAffaires, Philippine Embassy in Beijing (1976-1978) *Philippine Consul\nGeneral, Houston, Texas (1979-1986) *Assistant Secretary for Asian and Pacific\nAffairs and ASEAN Senior Official of the Philippines(1986-1988) *Ambassador\nExtraordinary and Plenipotentiary to Malaysia (1989-1992) *Undersecretary of\nForeign Affairs and ASEAN Senior Official of the Philippines (1992-1997)\n*Professor, Asian Institute of Management, Manila, the Philippines (2003-2004)\n","linknr":185,"url":"Rodolfo_Severino_Jr.","recorded":1375090484,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Rodolfo_Severino,_Jr.&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Rodolfo_Severino,_Jr.&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Rodolfo_Severino,_Jr.","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Rodolfo_Severino_Jr.&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/List_of_Secretaries-General_of_the_Association_of_Southeast_Asian_Nations","/wiki/Association_of_Southeast_Asian_Nations","/wiki/Ajit_Singh_(Malaysian_diplomat)","/wiki/Ong_Keng_Yong","/wiki/Philippines","/wiki/Alma_mater","/wiki/Ateneo_de_Manila_University","/wiki/Paul_H._Nitze_School_of_Advanced_International_Studies","/wiki/Diplomat","/wiki/Catholic_Church","/wiki/Filipino_people","/wiki/Diplomat","/wiki/